						               													<description>From Valmy to Waterloo is a miniatures game detailing warfare in Europe from 1792 through 1815.  The game is divided into 2 parts, grand tactical and tactical.  At the grand tactical level, the player is able to take on the role of Army Commander issuing orders to Corps and Divisions.  At the tactical level allows for players to implement the orders of the Army commander.  Written orders make up a very important part of the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Rules are somewhat complex, but once mastered give an accurate picture of conflict in the time period.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Game includes:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     104-page rule booklet&amp;#10;     56-page Army Lists and Scenarios booklet&amp;#10;     18-page reference-sheet booklet&amp;#10;     4 reference cards&amp;#10;     2 template sheets (to be photocopied onto clear acetate)&amp;#10;     1 orders sheet&amp;#10;     2 half-sheets of counters&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Scenarios:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Golymin 1807&amp;#10;     Linz 1809&amp;#10;     Wagram - first day 1809&amp;#10;     Quatre Bras 1815&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
